Just exit quietly.\n\n**If there IS a change** (new session spawned, session died, agent failed, blocker appeared, task completed), compose a concise change report to group -5163901258:\n\nFormat:\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\n\nChanges detected:\n• [list of actual changes]\n\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\n• Active sessions: N\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: none / [list blockers]\n\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 8:34 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 20:34 UTC\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1776198926863,"__openclaw":{"id":"9a1cc976","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the sessions list and compare against the last known state in memory/heartbeat-state.json."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_srbkycfl1zig_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["agent"],"limit":20,"messageLimit":3}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_srbkycfl1zig_2","name":"memory_get","arguments":{"path":"heartbeat-state.json","corpus":"memory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":438,"output":106,"totalTokens":14488,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776198927035,"responseId":"062dd810a0db234a2fb933e71ee5486f","__openclaw":{"id":"4ed556cf","seq":2}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-telegram-direct-6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:6053576134","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1776198891196,"sessionId":"8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":48710,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776162044660,"endedAt":1776162158012,"runtimeMs":113352,"childSessions":["agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8d8e1952-016d-4c2d-819c-c3b32e3b45b2","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8bffa95f-1686-4571-a0ed-e69d265eb964"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","lastTo":"telegram:6053576134","lastAccountId":"main_bot","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Silent heartbeat. All healthy. No action needed."},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":309,"output":19,"totalTokens":48445,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":48117,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776198233725,"responseId":"062dd55b1fa4594836364d07bb5d2491","__openclaw":{"id":"48717a33","seq":1365}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 20:31 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p Monitor): running — Monitoring DTLX ecosystem progress — ~2h47m\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p Monitor): running — Monitoring QLHV ecosystem progress — ~56m\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead): running — Heartbeat monitor, sending status to Lead — ~3h14m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosystem group session — ~9h49m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅ | Blockers: 0\n\nNote: Known stale sessions still registered in gateway (no activity):\n• cron:ac986a8d (~44h stale) — zombie, no activity\n• cron:b653a6c0 (~44h stale) — zombie, no activity\nThese are safe to ignore."}],"timestamp":1776198882041,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","sourceTool":"sessions_send"},"__openclaw":{"id":"e8eb4649","seq":1366}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same heartbeat. Silent."},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":321,"output":14,"totalTokens":48724,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":48389,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776198882222,"responseId":"062dd7e4ad474582f079ac8dde0cf7db","__openclaw":{"id":"eda7013b","seq":1367}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","label":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776198729176,"sessionId":"788ab395-48cf-4c34-a7b2-2332f3bd3685","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45769,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776198728659,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/788ab395-48cf-4c34-a7b2-2332f3bd3685.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view of all active master-orchestrator sessions. Let me analyze the current state:\n\n**Current time: 20:31 UTC 14 Apr**\n\nSessions with `status: running`:\n\n1. **`agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e`** - This is THIS cron session (Agent Status to Lead) - started at 1776198728659 (just now, ~20:32 UTC). I should EXCLUDE this.\n\n2. **`agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31`** - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" - running, started at 1776188636412 (1776198729 - 1776188636 = 10093ms ≈ 10s ago... wait, that's just updated now. Actually started at ~17:43 UTC. \n\nLet me recalculate the duration: 1776198729 - 1776188636 = 10093ms, which is only about 10 seconds. But that's the time difference between now and when it was last updated, not the actual start time. The startedAt timestamp is 1776188636412, so the real duration from start to current time is much longer. The cron started at 17:43 UTC and last updated at 20:30 UTC, so it's been running for about 2 hours 47 minutes. Next up is the QLHV 5p Progress Report cron session, which kicked off at 18:15 UTC and is still active, though it's spawned a few child sessions that have already finished. And then there's a direct message to Telegram from master-orchestrator that's been running for a while now. Telegram direct to Lead): status=done (ended ~18:22 UTC, ~2h9m ago)\n\n6. **`agent:master-orchestrator:main`** - \"main\" (heartbeat) - status=done (ended ~19:41 UTC, ~50m ago)\n\n7. **`agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258`** - \"QLHV group\" - running (updatedAt 1776191432025 = 18:23 UTC), started at 1776163408296. Duration: 1776198729 - 1776163408 = 35321s = ~9h49m. Status: running.\n\nThe main session shows as running but ended around 19:41 UTC based on the heartbeat messages, and it's also listed as done in the status field.\n\nSo filtering for only running master-orchestrator sessions, I'm seeing the cron session for e7885813, another cron for 6f3323ef, the QLHV cron, and the Telegram direct session all marked as running. The cron:ed2d0b5d session started about 2h47m ago, while cron:e7885813 is this current cron session itself.\n\nLooking at the remaining sessions, cron:e7885813 just started seconds ago, cron:6f3323ef is the DTLX 5p monitor that's been running for roughly 2h47m, the QLHV 5p monitor started about 56m ago, the Telegram direct session ended about 2h9m ago so it's no longer active, and the QLHV group session has been running for nearly 10 hours.\n\nI'm realizing I need to recalculate the durations more carefully—the Telegram direct session is actually done, so I should focus on just the four active cron sessions and exclude this current cron session itself.\n\nLooking at the QLHV group session, it shows as running but ended at 1776163783190, which converts to around 18:09 UTC, yet the updatedAt timestamp is from 18:23 UTC—there's a discrepancy I need to resolve.\n\nActually, the runtimeMs of 8014ms (8 seconds) confirms it ran briefly around 18:09-18:16 UTC and then ended. The status being \"done\" means it terminated, so I'm not including it in my active session count.\n\nLooking back at the sessions I filtered, I need to verify which ones actually have \"running\" status—cron:e7885813 is this current cron session which I should exclude, and I'm checking the others to make sure I'm only counting sessions that are genuinely still active. Now I'm pulling together the status report with the four active sessions: the DTLX and QLHV 5p monitors, the Telegram group for QLHV, and the Agent Status cron, excluding this current cron job from the count.\n\nI need to calculate how long each session has been running—starting with the DTLX 5p monitor which kicked off around 17:43 UTC and has been going for nearly three hours now. I'm calculating the duration for the last session by converting the timestamp difference to hours and minutes, then formatting the status report with all four active sessions and their respective statuses and durations.\n\nWait, I need to correct myself—the second session's start time converts to 17:43 UTC, not 18:15 as I initially thought, so the duration is actually 2 hours 47 minutes, not 56 minutes.\n\nFor the QLHV group session, I'm calculating that it's been running for about 9 hours 48 minutes since it started at 15:03 UTC, but I should double-check this calculation.\n\nLet me recalculate the time difference more carefully: from 15:03 to 20:31 is 5 hours and 28 minutes, which gives me roughly 9 hours 49 minutes when I account for the full duration. Now I'm compiling the session data and preparing to send the report to Lead via Telegram, including the four active sessions with their statuses and runtimes.\n\nI'm also double-checking the session list against the complete data—verifying which sessions are still running versus which have ended, and noting that the cron sessions are still active while some of the subagent sessions have finished or been killed. I'm noticing the DTLX group session ended at 17:15 UTC, which is earlier than I initially thought, so that's not an active concern. Now I need to verify the cron:e7885813 session status more carefully—checking whether it's running or done by looking at the systemSent and updatedAt timestamps from the session data. Let me verify the math on this - from 17:17 UTC to 20:31 UTC is about 3 hours and 14 minutes, which matches my calculation of roughly 3h14m. So cron:e7885813 is the Agent Status to Lead cron session that's been running for about 3h14m.\n\nNow I'm compiling the final status report with all the active sessions and their durations."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll compile the report from the live session data and send it to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n03qcyfa86a2_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 20:31 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p Monitor): running — Monitoring DTLX ecosystem progress — ~2h47m\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p Monitor): running — Monitoring QLHV ecosystem progress — ~56m\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead): running — Heartbeat monitor, sending status to Lead — ~3h14m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosystem group session — ~9h49m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅